1)  cp -r project /home/aart/backup

        cp → copy command
        -r → recursive (copies folders and files inside it)

    Using SCP : 
    scp -r project divi@192.168.1.20:/home/aart/

      scp → secure copy using SSH

     -r → copy entire folder recursively

     username → user in remote system

     remote_ip → destination machine IP

2) Through FTP 
   sudo apt install vsftpd
   Starting service 
   sudo systemctl start vsftpd
   Connecting to ftp 
   ftp 192.168.1.20
   Upload file (PUT)
   put file.txt
  Download file (GET)
   get file.txt
  To exit ftp 
   exit 

  SFTP (Secure FTP)
  sftp username@192.168.1.20
  Commands inside SFTP

   put file.txt
   get file.txt
   ls
   cd
   exit


3) Using tcpdump (Linux)

Capture packets

sudo tcpdump

Capture specific interface

sudo tcpdump -i eth0

Capture ICMP packets

sudo tcpdump icmp




5) Duplicate IP means two devices use the same IP address in the network.

Problems:
    Network conflict
    Packet loss
    Connection instability
    Devices become unreachable
Detection:
    System shows message like
    IP address conflict detected
Resolution:
    Assign unique IP addresses
    Use DHCP instead of manual IP


